				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mu _{max}$$\end{document}μmax, the aerobic condition with fructose (OXY-FYP) and its anaerobic counterpart (ANA-FYP) both demonstrated relatively similar growth rates, around 0.154 and 0.144, respectively. However, the aerobic glucose condition (OXY-GYP) displayed a lower growth rate of 0.080, while the anaerobic glucose condition (ANA-GYP) showed an even lower rate of 0.074. Intriguingly, media with a combination of fructose and glucose (OXY-GYP-F and ANA-GYP-F) exhibited the highest growth rates, with values of 0.285 and 0.301, respectively.

Turning to the \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
